snippet.textDisplay:
Finally someone who understands why Americans buy tap water in bottles.

1. Convenience. We love to grab a bottle and go. My family always has a few in the car. On road trip vacations we'll throw a whole case of water in the trunk.

2 Taste, a lot of municipal waters taste like ass. Nearly always perfectly clean and healthy, but the mineral contents can make some taste like an old sock. -

snippet.textDisplay: Well, great for this amazing information. But it's in the past. Let's concentrate on the present situation. ;-) Is there any way to find out what kind of water so many companies sell now and they label it "Mineral Water"? Is it mineral or tap water? Can those people who work in those factories kindly tell us? Or can you Tom, make some kind of research about it? The problem is that they don't list where they bottle their water. Consumers nowadays have to be some kind of researchers to find out the origin of a given product... It's preposterous.  And why the heck Aldi in UK is selling grapes from India? I bought a pack of white grapes recently and the grapes had some small black spots on them like some kind of disease...I've never seen anything like it. Thank you for your hard work and amazing videos. Nina.

snippet.textDisplay: Bottled water here in the states or at least here in Vegas is a MASSIVE money maker. You would think our water coming from the tap is brown by the way they buy massive quantities of this stuff. Fact is Vegas from the tap here in Vegas is just fine, clear and clean. Coming from the East and living with well water, it was only natural I would have a filter system in place. I bought this house with its huge filtration system already in place. It came with two very large filers, one carbon and one paper. I was to change them yearly....but I didn't and it was 5 years before I did. The white paper filter was still white, not brown, not gray, but white. That is an indication the water coming into this house is VERY CLEAN. So this crazy thing about buying tons of bottled water to me makes no sense.Bottled water here in the states is a MAJOR money maker...the day I pay $6.00 for a small bottle of flavored tap water will be a cold day in hell.
